When this Bill was up for con- sideration before, it was suggested that possibly a claim might be made against the government for the right that we are now taking to,run over the Canada Atlantic, without reference to the fact whether We used that right or not. Provided that no compensation shall be pay— able for such running powers unless and until the same are actually exercised, and then only for such exercise.
